<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 4:40AM EDT  by NWS Wakefield</headline>
<description>...Patchy dense fog this morning...
Patchy dense fog has developed across portions of the Eastern
Shore, southeast Virginia, and northeast North Carolina.
Visibilities will average less than 2 miles. Locally reduced
visibilities may drop to one quarter mile or below. When driving,
use caution and be prepared for rapidly changing visibilities, use
low beams, and slow down.
Fog should diminish after sunrise.</description>
